# web-dashboard code

## Scope of edits

- Change only what the request needs. No drive-by refactors, comment stripping, or unrelated formatting.
- Match existing naming, imports, component patterns, and type style in the touched files.

## Where things live

- **UI**: `src/pages/`, `src/components/`, `src/layouts/` — React 18, React Router, TanStack Query, Zustand where already used.
- **HTTP/API client**: `src/api/` — extend existing modules instead of ad-hoc `fetch` in components when an API module exists.
- **Shared types**: `src/types/api.ts` (and nearby) — align new shapes with existing types.
- **Node server**: `server/` (entry `server/index.js`) — keep DB and route patterns consistent with `server/db.js` / `server/pgdb.js`.
- **SQL migrations**: `server/migrations/`.
- **Supabase**: `supabase/functions/`, client helpers under `src/lib/supabase.ts` when integrating.

## Quality

- After substantive edits, run `npm run lint` or check linter diagnostics for touched files when feasible.
- Prefer reusing utilities under `src/lib/` over duplicating logic.
